[[File:Cambridge_Science_Festival_logo.png|thumb|The 2015 Cambridge Science Festival logo.]] {{for|the science festival initiated and cosponsored by the [[MIT Museum]]|MIT Museum#Cambridge Science Festival}}
The '''Cambridge Science Festival''' is a series of events typically held annually in March in [[Cambridge]], [[England]] and is the United Kingdom's largest free [[science festival]].<ref name="bbc">{{cite web|title=University of Cambridge Science Festival 2011|publisher=BBC News|url=http://bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-cambridgeshire-12759607|accessdate=21 March 2015}}</ref> The festival attracts more than 30,000 visitors to over 250 events.<ref>{{cite web|title=About - www.sciencefestival.cam.ac.uk|url=http://www.sciencefestival.cam.ac.uk/about|accessdate=21 March 2015}}</ref> University researches and students open their lecture halls and laboratories to the general public, and hold Talks, Exhibitions and Demonstrations, mostly free of charge.<ref name="bbc" />
Started in 1994 by scientists of the [[University of Cambridge]] and backed by local businesses, the festival was inspired by ''National Science Week'' and is aimed making science and engineering more accessible, showcasing research performed at Cambridge University, and encouraging young people to pursue careers in engineering and science.<ref>{{cite web|title=Two exciting decades of scientific fun and games|publisher=Cambridge News|url=http://cambridge-news.co.uk/exciting-decades-scientific-fun-games/story-22498061-detail/story.html|accessdate=21 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=21st Cambridge Science Festival hopes to inspire the next generation of scientists|publisher=Anglia - ITV News|url=http://itv.com/news/anglia/update/2015-03-10/21st-cambridge-science-festival-hopes-to-inspire-the-next-generation-of-scientists|accessdate=21 March 2015}}</ref>
The 21st festival ran from 9 to 22 March 2015 and featured themes based on light science and technology to mark [[UNESCO]]'s ''[[International Year of Light]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Reaching out in the International Year of Light|url=http://optics.org/news/6/3/1|accessdate=21 March 2015}}</ref> {{-}}
